data.text:
I have noticed a SQLlite db, which is okay with me but I don't think it would be great for production.

Here is why! because you have to access the data from a file locally on the system rather than being able to grab the information anywhere. Meaning we cant share info on the fly unless we sync the file across the computers.

In example, I have awesome sauce in my DB, but you do not have it in your DB!

Care to test it??????
